{"lemma":"نِسْبَةٍ","slug":"نِسْبَةٍ","root":"ن.س.ب","root_slug":"ن-س-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-س-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adv","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":10},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n39691","n39700","n39701"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%90%D8%B3%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of نَسَبَ (nasaba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"relationship, affiliation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"connection, relation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"agreement"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ratio, proportion"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rate","examples":[{"text":"اِنْخَفَضَتْ نِسْبَةُ ٱلْبِطَالَةِ فِي ٱلسَّنَوَاتِ ٱلْأَخِيرَةِ.","english":"The unemployment rate has decreased in recent years."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"percentage","examples":[{"text":"تَدْرُسُ نِسْبَةٌ كَبِيرَةٌ مِنَ ٱلشَّبَابِ فِي ٱلْخَارِجِ.","english":"A big percentage of young people study abroad."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"nisba, a common suffix to form adjectives of relation or pertinence, e.g. ـي (-ī, -iyy) m and ـيَة (-íyya) f."},{"pos":"adv","gloss":"in proportion to, in comparison with"},{"pos":"adv","gloss":"in allusion to, after (as in \"named after\")","examples":[{"text":"جَامِعُ الفَاتِحُ سُمَّى نِسْبَةً لِلسُّلْطَانِ مُحَمَّدِ الفَاتِحِ","english":"Fatih Mosque was named after the sultan Mehmed the Conqueror."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of نَسَبَ (nasaba).\n\nAdverbial accusative of نِسْبَة (nisba, “relationship”)."},"ipa":["/nis.ba/","/nis.ba.tan/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n39691","headword_ar":"نَسَبَهُ","root":"nsb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasobN","text_ar":"نَسْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nisobapN","text_ar":"نِسْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) and aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasabN","text_ar":"نَسَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nisobapN","text_ar":"نِسْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He mentioned his"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. another's]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relationship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lineage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"genealogy"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, K;) saying,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is such a one, the son of such a one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is of such a tribe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"city;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of such an art,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a trade;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lb. T.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasabahu","text_ar":"نَسَبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasobN","text_ar":"نَسْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He traced up his"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. another's]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lineage to his greatest ancestor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasabahu","text_ar":"نَسَبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"?,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He asked him to mention,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tell him, his relationship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lineage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"genealogy"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilayohi","text_ar":"اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jalasotu A_ilayohi fanasabaniY qaA@notasabotu","text_ar":"جَلَسْتُ اـِلَيْهِ فَنَسَبَنِى قَا@نْتَسَبْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I sat by him, and he asked me to tell him my lineage; so I mentioned my lineage to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahaA","text_ar":"لَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasabatonaA faA@notasabonaA","text_ar":"نَسَبَتْنَا فَا@نْتَسَبْنَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She asked us to tell her our lineage; so we mentioned our lineage to her"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IAar, from a trad.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasabahu AlY fulaAnK","text_ar":"نَسَبَهُ الى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He asserted him to be related to such a one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he referred his lineage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"origin, to such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b7-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He referred the origin"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"derivation of his name to such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b8-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He attributed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ascribed, it to such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"See, for ex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sad~aqa","text_ar":"صَدَّقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*~aba","text_ar":"كَذَّبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Msb. ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasabahu A_ilaY ka*aA","text_ar":"نَسَبَهُ اـِلَى كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He referred its origin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the origin"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"derivation of its name, to such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b10-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He attributed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ascribed, it to such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b11- ]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasabahu A_ilaY fulaAnK","text_ar":"نَسَبَهُ اـِلَى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He named him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called him, in relation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reference, to such a one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning an ancestor: and in like manner, in relation, or reference, to a tribe, a town or district, an art or trade, &c. See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nisobapN","text_ar":"نِسْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasabahu A_laY k*aA","text_ar":"نَسَبَهُ اـلَى كذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He named it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called it, in relation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reference, to such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b13-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasaba A_ilayohi ka*aA","text_ar":"نَسَبَ اـِلَيْهِ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and, by inversion,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasabahu A_ilaY","text_ar":"نَسَبَهُ اـِلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aA","text_ar":"كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (see S and K, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jhl","text_ar":"جهل"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He attributed"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imputed to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"charged him with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accused him of, such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, a fault &c. Both phrases are often used as signifying thus by classical writers, and in the present day.] ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasaba biAlomaroA^api","text_ar":"نَسَبَ بِالْمَرْاَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasiybN","text_ar":"نَسِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasabN","text_ar":"نَسَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manosabapN","text_ar":"مَنْسَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ab~aba bihaA","text_ar":"شَبَّبَ بِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; q. v.; (S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He mentioned the woman in an amatory manner, in the beginning"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prelude"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a poem:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$b~b","text_ar":"شبّب"},{"kind":"text","text":":)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he mentioned the woman in amatory language, in the beginning of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSiydap","text_ar":"قَصِيدَة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and then turned to the object of praise:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for it is a general rule to commence a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qSydp","text_ar":"قصيدة"},{"kind":"text","text":"in praise of a king, or hero, or the like, with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nsyb","text_ar":"نسيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the transition from this is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~axal~uSu","text_ar":"التَّخَلُّصُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiqotaDaba","text_ar":"اِقْتَضَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] (IKh:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he mentioned the woman in his poem, describing her as characterized by beauty and youth &c.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"describing her as characterized by good qualities, whether truly"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"falsely."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z.) This phrase and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasaba Alr~ajula","text_ar":"نَسَبَ الرَّجُلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"both signify description; the latter signifying “ he described the man with relation to his father, or his city or country, or"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2787},{"kind":"text","text":"the like; ” and the former phrase,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he described the woman as characterized by beauty and youth and love"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affection &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrst.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasiybN","text_ar":"نَسِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also employed to signify the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"describing of the places where the objects of love have taken up their abode in the season of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyE","text_ar":"رَبِيع"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and at other times, and the lover's longing to meet them and be united with them, and what else is comprised in the signification of the words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta$obiybN","text_ar":"تَشْبِيبٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gazalN","text_ar":"غَزَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (MF.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gazila","text_ar":"غَزِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gazalN","text_ar":"غَزَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","K","L","IKh","Lb"]},{"entry_id":"n39700","headword_ar":"نِسْبَةٌ","root":"nsb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Relation; proportion; comparison;"},{"kind":"text","text":"with respect to quantity, or measure, and the like. See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasabN","text_ar":"نَسَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binisobapi ka*aA","text_ar":"بِنِسْبَةِ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In proportion to such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nisobapu AlEa$arapi A_ilaY AlmiAy^api","text_ar":"نِسْبَةُ العَشَرَةِ اـِلَى المِايَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The proportion of ten to a hundred is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that of a tenth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) ―         -b4-  [You also say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAln~isobapi A_ilaY ka*aA","text_ar":"بِالنِّسْبَةِ اـِلَى كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In relation to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in comparison with, such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nisobapN","text_ar":"نِسْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A name of relation to a father, mother, tribe, town"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"district, art"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trade, &c.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalawiY~N","text_ar":"عَلَوِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faATimiY~N","text_ar":"فَاطِمِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qura$iY~N","text_ar":"قُرَشِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mak~iY~N","text_ar":"مَكِّىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawohariY~N","text_ar":"جَوْهَرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] ending with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y~","text_ar":"ىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". A more general name of this kind should precede a more particular one: thus you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqura$iY~u AlhaA$imiY~u","text_ar":"القُرَشِىُّ الهَاشِمِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and it is better that a name of relation to a tribe should precede one of relation to a town or the like: thus you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqura$iY~u Almak~iY~u","text_ar":"القُرَشِىُّ المَكِّىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". It is said that the Arabs originally called themselves by such names only in relation to tribes; and that, when they took up their abodes in cultivated lands and in cities, they borrowed names of relation to towns and the like from the Persians and Copts. (Msb.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nisobapN","text_ar":"نِسْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munaAsabapN","text_ar":"مُنَاسَبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanaAsubN","text_ar":"تَنَاسُبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Resemblance; similarity; conformity; analogy; correspondence; suitableness; fitness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.) Ex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayona Al$~ayoy^ayoni nsbpN","text_ar":"بَيْنَ الشَّيْيَيْنِ نسبةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mnAsbpN","text_ar":"مناسبةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tnAsbN","text_ar":"تناسبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Between the two things is a resemblance, &c."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonahumaA nsbpN qariybapN","text_ar":"بَيْنَهُمَا نسبةٌ قَرِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Between them two is a near resemblance, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nisobapN Hukomiy~apN","text_ar":"نِسْبَةٌ حُكْمِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relation of a predicate to its subject"},{"kind":"text","text":"(in books on logic).]"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n39701","headword_ar":"نُسْبَةٌ","root":"nsb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasabN","text_ar":"نَسَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}